Package: Exercise6
Type: Package
Title: Converting measurements of length
Version: 0.1.1
Author: Raphael John (12548296)
Maintainer: Raphael John <r.john@campus.lmu.de>
Description: Converting measurements of length (metric and imperial). 
  Input can be given in differnt forms, and arrays can also be converted.
  Conversion - input a numeric, the old and the new unit.
  Arrayconversion - input an array of numerics, the old and the new unit.
  Strconversion - input a string with the value and unit and choose if the 
  output should be a numeric or a string with value and unit as well.
  Arraystrconversion - input an array of Strings with the Value and unit and 
  choose if the output should be a numeric or a string with value and unit as well.
  The following units are possible -
  "twip", "thou", "inch", "hand", "foot", "yard", "chain", "furlong", "mile", 
  "league", "millimeter", "centimeter", "meter", "kilometer"
  And the following abbreviations can also be used - 
  "twip", "th", "in", "hh", "ft", "yd", "ch", "fur", "mi", "lea", "mm", "cm", "m", "km"
